ORIA EN FOTOS \u2013 MOTAGUA|accessdate=15 August 2017|year=2017|publisher=[[La Tribuna (Honduras)|La Tribuna]]}}</ref>  Motagua currently plays in the [[Liga Nacional de F\u00fatbol Profesional de Honduras|Honduran Liga Nacional]], the top tier of Honduran football.  They have not been out of the top tier since 1965, the year the league was inaugurated.  They have also been involved in [[CONCACAF]] football since they qualified to the [[CONCACAF Champions League|CONCACAF Champions' Cup]] in [[1969 CONCACAF Champions' Cup|1969]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cacups69.html|title=Central American Club Competitions 1969|accessdate=22 August 2013|year=2013|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]}}</ref>\n\nThis list encompasses the major honours won by Motagua and records set by the club, their managers and their players.  The player records section includes details of the club's leading goalscorers and those who have made most appearances in first-team competitions.  It also records notable achievements by Motagua players on the international stage.\n\n''All stats accurate as of match played 7 March 2020.''\n\n==Honours==\n[[F.C. Motagua]] is the second most successful club in [[Honduras]] having won 16 domestic leagues since the inauguration of the [[Liga Nacional de F\u00fatbol de Honduras|Honduran Liga Nacional]] in 1965\u201366.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://motaguacampeon.weebly.com/historia-del-club.html|title=HISTORIA Motagua Campe\u00f3n|accessdate=5 December 2007|year=2007|publisher=Motagua Campe\u00f3n}}</ref>\n\n{{#lst:F.C. Motagua|Achievements}}\n\n==Players==\n{{see also|:Category:F.C. Motagua players}}\n\n===200+ Appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Player !! Years !! {{tooltip|App.|Appearances}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[J\u00fanior Izaguirre]] || align=center | 1997\u20132005, 2011\u20132016 || align=center | 404<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laprensa.hn/deportes/779050-410/j%C3%BAnior-izaguirre-leyenda-en-el-motagua|title=J\u00fanior Izaguirre, leyenda en el Motagua|accessdate=22 December 2014|year=2014|publisher=[[La Prensa (Honduras)|La Prensa]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[\u00c1ngel Obando]] || align=center | 1972\u20131986 || align=center | 300\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Milton Reyes]] || align=center | 1997\u20132002, 2005\u20132011 || align=center | 291\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Ram\u00f3n Maradiaga]] || align=center | 1975\u20131982, 1989\u20131990 || align=center | 287\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Luis Alberto Reyes|Luis Reyes]] || align=center | 1976\u20131985 || align=center | 275\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Omar Elvir]] || align=center | 2010\u2013 || align=center | 275\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Rub\u00e9n Guifarro]] || align=center | 1967\u20131984 || align=center | 260\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Amado Guevara]] || align=center | 1994\u20132000, 2007\u20132008, 2010\u20132013 || align=center | 258\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Ninrrol Medina]] || align=center | 1993\u20132000, 2001\u20132002 || align=center | 243\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Juan Pablo Montes|Juan Montes]] || align=center | 2013\u2013 || align=center | 240\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Wilmer Crisanto]] || align=center | 2014\u2013 || align=center | 222\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Carlos Discua]] || align=center | 2011\u20132015, 2016\u20132018 || align=center | 221\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Herna\u00edn Arz\u00fa]] || align=center | 1988\u20131998 || align=center | 212\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Iv\u00e1n Guerrero]] || align=center | 1996\u20132010, 2002\u20132004, 2009\u20132011 || align=center | 210\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Reinieri Mayorqu\u00edn]] || align=center | 2014\u2013 || align=center | 200\n|}\n\n===Top 10 scorers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Player !! Years !! {{tooltip|Goals|Goals scored}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[Rubilio Castillo]] || align=center | 2014\u20132018 || align=center | 88\n|-\n| {{flagicon|HON}} [[\u00c1ngel Obando]] || align=center | 1972\u20131986 || align=center | 77\n